FBIS4-21695 "jptnd009___94082" JPRS-TND-94-009 JPRS PROLIFERATION ISSUES 5 April 1994 INTERNATIONAL Tokyo `Unable To Confirm' Perry Claims on DPRK Nuke Program Tokyo `Unable To Confirm' Perry Claims on DPRK Nuke Program PM0504140794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Apr 94 First Edition p 6 PM0504140794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [ITAR-TASS report from the "Yesterday, Today, and Tomorrow" column: "Does North Korea Have a Specific Program?"] [Text] Tokyo is unable to confirm the statement by U.S. Secretary of Defense William Perry that the DPRK has started implementing a program which will enable it to produce at least twelve nuclear devices a year within two to three years. An ITAR-TASS correspondent was informed of this by a senior Japanese Foreign Ministry official. He observed that he did not know the reasons which enabled the U.S. secretary of defense to make such a statement during an interview with a U.S. television company Sunday [3 April].
